visser@ph.tn.tudelft.nl (Boudewijn W. Ch. Visser) writes:

>I remember reading that the estimate for factoring rsa 129 was about
>40 quadrillion (sp?) (40 * 10^15 ?) years.
>I think that Rivest,Shamir and Adleman knew very well what the state-of-the
>art algorithms and hardware were,and I hate to think that their guess was off
>by a factor of about 10^16.

After RSA129 was recently broken, one of these fellows said something to
the effect of "I pulled that number out of my ass."  He regretted making
such a wild guess.

